mcp-safe-fetch
==============

This product includes software developed by third parties:

Layer-2 sanitizer (chain attribution)
-------------------------------------
The Python sanitizer at `src/mcp_safe_fetch/sanitizer.py` is vendored
from the companion safe-fetch project, which in turn ported the logic
from the original mcp-safe-fetch project by Tim Stark.

Direct upstream (vendored from):
  Project:  safe-fetch
  Source:   https://github.com/sharkyger/safe-fetch
  Path:     src/safe_fetch/sanitizer.py
  License:  MIT
  Copyright (c) 2026 Sharky

Original upstream (logic origin):
  Project:  mcp-safe-fetch (timstarkk)
  Source:   https://github.com/timstarkk/mcp-safe-fetch
  Commit:   e82724c9b9535aff6c2cc102aa17abd16b726b96
  License:  MIT
  Copyright (c) 2025 Tim Stark

Both upstream licenses are MIT and are preserved below.

Refresh procedure: when safe-fetch's sanitizer.py changes, re-vendor
into this repo with `cp ../safe-fetch/src/safe_fetch/sanitizer.py
src/mcp_safe_fetch/sanitizer.py` (or equivalent) and re-attribute via
the header comment. When timstarkk's upstream changes, evaluate
whether to port through safe-fetch first or directly into this repo.

Search query→URL validators
---------------------------
The search input validators in `src/mcp_safe_fetch/search.py`
(`template_error`, `query_error`, `build_search_url`, `_has_control_chars`)
are vendored byte-identical from safe-fetch's `src/safe_fetch/search.py`
(MIT, Copyright (c) 2026 Sharky) so the fleet validates searches
identically. Config loading is adapted to this project's container model
(environment variables only, no host config file). Original safe-fetch
search support has no third-party lineage.

